external_knowledge:
- "NFL" stands for the National Football League;
- "Home games" refer to games played at the team's own stadium;
- "Average attendance" is calculated by dividing the total attendance by the number of completed home games.

- "stands atop the podium" refers to the team ranked first;
- "the most victories" refers to the highest number of wins;
- "the fewest defeats" refers to the lowest number of losses.

- "flown the flag of victory" refers to teams that have played in completed games;
- "home nest" refers to home games;
- "distant land" refers to away games;
- "neither side claimed the home or away title" refers to games where both home_team and away_team flags are set to 0.

- "Crown jewel" refers to the most prestigious or valuable item in a collection;
- "Home crowds" refers to the spectators attending the games when the team plays at their home stadium;
- "Drawing the largest average number of spectators" means the stadium has the highest average attendance for home games.

- "the roar of the crowd" refers to a high crowd noise level;
- "more than 45,000 fans in attendance" refers to a large audience;
- "whether playing at home or away" indicates that the condition applies to both home and away games.
